content: A bit too easy at the start, but gets really tough later on. Great game!

It's good, like a cross between Arknights and Dungeon Keeper, it has absolutely no IAP and everything in the game can be earned for free. The difficulty is alright, not too easy or hard, but you can challenge yourself with the runes that buff enemies.
Great game! You get the whole thing for 3 dollars. No ads. Endless kudos to the devs for taking this route these days
Very good game. Just no real incentive for replay...which is a shame with such good gameplay. So after 10-12 hours maybe..game is finished.
Great twist on tower defense. Some decently tough levels as well, and mechanics of game allow you to change your strategy and re purpose your power ups as needed for each level.

It's fun, but too difficult at higher levels. The rate of earning gems to advance traps is too little. And the reward for leveling up isn't enough since there is no way to decrease the price of traps short of spending gems. Dungeon warfare 2 is a much better game in those asprcts
Great tower defense game, with unique features.
Challenging!
Great game :) Hazard-like mechanics are limited, just pure gameplay.
Best TD I've ever played. Buy it. Better than Rush.
Extremely well done and a ton of fun
Wonderful game! I really like games that you can upgrade stuff and really see your progression.

An excellent game. Hours of play time. Fun, challenging, rewarding. Offline and no ads. Just like a classic PC game. If you're into life like graphics and cut scenes then this might not be for you, but if rewarding gameplay is what you're after then download! One request to the dev team, please can we have a save feature for endless levels??
I love this game. Set traps and kill guys.

Along with Dungeon Defense, these tower defense games inject much needed flair in their respective genres. I cannot begin to describe how exhilarating it is to watch carefully layed out traps make hamburger meat of the unfortunate adventurers lining up to invade my dungeons! The game weaves specialty "runes" that can be applied to each stage, which enforces unique challenges in exchange more experience points, giving players rewards for replaying stages previously won. A staple of tower defense.
Best RPG TD since Gemcraft!
I love this game. Yes you will struggle in the begining but the more younplay the better it gets.

Played it through. Play pass. A different kind of tower defence, but guess it will appeal to those sort of players. Innovative and enjoyed it. Wish the graphics were a bit better. Will prob buy the second one. Edit:forgot to mention NO IAP thank christ for that
Fun and really enjoyable throwing enemies down holes or pools of lava

I've tried a ton of tower defense games and this one hits just the right spot for me. Lots of levels, lots of modifiers, lots of towers. Only complaint: no info on what the enemies actually do, but it's visually pretty easy to figure out so it's no biggie.
I'm totally hooked. Can be very challenging at times but sometimes you just need to find the right combination and then just watch the carnage
It's fun initially, then after a few levels (10?) I dont find it as fun, and dont feel like starting a new match
Solid Tower Defense!!!
One of the best TD games
Good gameplay will purchase the second one after I finish this one as a cheap Christmas present for myself
The best tower defense game on mobile by far. Worth the price. Buy it, play it.
Love the dungeon feel to it. Great so far!

It was great but a few traps need to be buffed and I feel like I few need to be nerfed but I don't know which first of the spike trap not the floor one the one in the walls it should Pierce through any enemy no matter what may not kill him but it should Pierce through all the enemies in its rangebecause I view it as group killing power but when it shoots once every three seconds which may seem fast but it's not considering the things I'm trying to kill in a single hit
No ads. Seems really fun so far, decent bit of challenge. Love the art style.
Free defences games work better without glitches, no matter how good a game is if it does not work then it is no good
If you love tower games. I definitely recommend this one. I enjoy the game play. Its very easy to pick up on. I like dungeon the aspect more than the tower.
Awesome but gets boring rather quick in my opinion
Dungeon Warfare is one of the best tower defense games I have played
I'm having a blast with this game. The graphics makes me remember DOS games I played in my childhood.

You know those awesome ads that sometimes pop up with a little flash game with age of empire RTS elements, but the app being advertised is actually a micro transaction nightmare with no redeeming qualities? And you sit there and think, god, I wish I could just play a game that is a deeper more nuanced version of the ad? THIS IS THAT GAME. I honestly had lost hope in the mobile game industry to scratch that itch, but this is a shining example of the value in paying upfront for games, phenomenal
Best Tower defense ever !!!!
I really love this game. It has a great art style, amazing music, and it's really hard
Really amazing game, map, and towers
Magnificent game.
No ads, worth every penny. Plays like a nice chill tower defence, no super one use optional (wink wink) items in this game.
Great tower defence game with a Dungeon Keeper vibe. Keep those heroes out of your throne room!
A really interesting take on tower defense, really love the game
Brilliant tower defence game with loads of mechanics and level varience that keeps you engaged. Well worth playing.
Can you add the rest of the enemies in the encyclopedia please?
I really love this game. You did an amazing job. Still trying to beat the All Heroes Must Die level but I love how no matter how many times I play it I can keep coming up with new strategies.
It's a quintessential tower defense game for cheap, on mobile, with no hidden fees, gatcha mechanics, or ads..
Pains me to reduce a star but please update game for notched screen devices. I can only see the 2 digits of exp on right side top.
If you play one tower defense game it should be this. Fun physics based death, environment traps, fun yet challenging. No in app purchases!

Absolutely the best tower defense game series available on the play store. No ads or in-app mtx, just a quality indie title. Love that they went for their own pixel art style over the endless cartoon style TD games out there.
Fun TD gem. Challenging right from the start, but achievable when you attempt different strategies.
Great game! It is a tower defence game set in a dungeon, it starts off easy and give you a lot of difficulty options. The last level is very hard.
Edited for update. Fixed my freezes. Thank you, best tower defense game
Very entertaining
Morfun.

Wow. What a fantastic game we have here. No ads, no iAP. It almost feels strange nowadays, in a good way. This is a hardcore tower defense game with physics implemented right. Extremely difficult at higher difficult. Forces me to think of the best traps and paths. Thanks for this. Better yet, I was coming write this review and i found out there is version 2 of this game. Bought it.

I normally dont leave game reviews but I had to for this one. No pay to win. It's an incredibly detailed and repayable tower defense. It's an unconventional one in that the environment plays a large part of your strategy. I love how the weight of each enemy plays into the physics of it and you can add "runes" to increase difficulty. This is a perfect game in every way
Well made game. "Impressive"!!! Lots of fun.

Pay once and enjoy am actual game. Very well done, sounds are satisfying and the gameplay is as challenging as you want to make it. Mechanics are easy to grasp and each "trap" is well explained with a demonstration to boot.
Great game. Best tower defense. Gave it a lower rating because now it just crashes when I select some of the dungeons (Pixel 3a)

Epic tower defence that's balanced for different play styles and has an awesome late game skill tree mechanic that rewards replaying levels at a higher difficulty, I do not regret paying cash for this game and I'm a tight budget spender!

Tower defense like Dungeon Keeper in 8bit. Hilarious physics, using cannonpult to fling people off cliffs or into spikes is especially funny. Better than bloons. No IAP! Great indy dev doing it for the passion. Replayable with multiple ways to beat each level. Rewards clever tactics over button mashing. You can choose your style of play, and since I hate button mashing added to other TD, it's perfect. Play your way. Perhaps one of the greatest TD ever made, Dungeon Warfare is brilliant.
It's a great tower defense without any micro transactions. 100% buy to play üëç

Having played a lot of tower defenses over the years, this one is easily the best. Pace of play is great, skill curve is brilliantly adjustable with the rune system, replayability is excellent, and every turret feels like a critical addition whose utility is tightly entwined with the landscape at play. If you like tower defense games, you are doing yourself a disservice by not giving this game a go.
Excellent tower defense game that kept me coming back for hours. You can add customizers to levels to make them more difficult and worth more points.
Excellent tower defense and no in app purchases. Pay once and enjoy a well done game. Great job, devs.
The best tower defense game I've played - like a top down orcs must die, with clever traps and lots of challenge. Really excellent.
Best tower defense game ever. Flawless.

great, just like DW2, I highly reccomend for any TD fans.
this has to be one of the best Tower Defense games ever and no microtransactions.

Great game. 1 time purchase. Plenty of fun
fun but "hold pause" for the menu doesnt work. So every time i need to reset i have to reset the entire game.

Good game without microtransactions or ads. Like orgasm to humanity's last hope.

Best tower defense out there! I will be buying the second one but still have a long way to go in this one first, thanks devs superb! if you know the game Orcs Must Die on PC ps4 etc, this is like a top down version of that. if you like tower defense you can't go wrong.

content: Very enjoyable tower defense gameplay with a great old school PC game vibe
Definitely One Of Top Three Tower Defense Games.

I wet my feet with tower defence playing Kingdom Rush which was really enjoyable but this is simply sublime. Graphics reminiscent of oldskool arcade Gauntlet but much more gory and visceral. Contrary to another review, there seems to be many ways to defeat each level but the game does demand a large amount of creative thinking. The sound effects, physics and hammed up music perfectly compliment the theme of cartoon heroes charging to their bloody death in a demonic dungeon. Simple but clever.
Fantastic TD game!

content: Nonstop fun. I bought this game because I was tired of micro transactions and being forced to rely on waiting for cooldowns to beat a level instead of skill or strategy. If you are all about strategy this is the game for you.
Draws heavily from the Orcs Must Die series, and that's a good thing.
Amazing tower defense game. I had bought this just to try it and ended up falling in love with it.
Hard tower defense, no micro transactions, lots of maps, good customization between each map, ways to increase the difficulty.
great game, fun and challenging, without freemium gimmicks
its great.
Lots of fun and non-trivial optimal solutions!
A brilliant game! No 'play to win' at all, challenging and rewarding.
An incredibly engaging and well-designed tower defense. Worth more than the asking price which is nice.

I got the game and immediately had to refund. it would try to make me sign in with my Google account and have an option for username. I would fill this out (not even hit "done"), and it would bump me out to the Google account sign in page. I did this several times, gave up, and had to get a refund. This game looks pretty good, and this is probably just an issue with my phone or account or something, but I cannot even play.

OK this is one of my favorite Steam games ever but there's two really big issues with playing it on my phone. Because my phone's aspect ratio is larger than the app's, the app shoves itself to one side instead of being centered like other apps do. But worst of all, it stops YouTube picture in picture and background app audio. Please see if this is just a minor fix you could apply!!
The best td game I have ever played. 100% worth the upfront cost

Your app stops spotify from playing in the background so its either your terrible background music or nothing. Cheers i felt like listening to this bloke talk about his fullsick surfboard while on the train anyway.

I hate mobile games with all their pay to win garbage and general tacky, cheap, crapness. This game is something else, it's the only mobile game I've played longer than 5 minutes in about the past 3-4 years. Buy it right now, you will be hooked instantly.
I love this game on pc and phone.
A great tower defense game. No microtransactions, and a good difficultly ramp.

This is what an app game should be. The first appeal is that there is no mechanic built around you as the player paying money. Pay once and never think about money again. Then, after playing, I was surprised that this game seemed to bring novel twists to the genre along with great production quality. As a bonus, when I'm playing with sound, the sound effects are incredible. Thanks for a great game, team!
Fantastic game! Very polished! No in-app purchases. No ads. Just one payment and you get it all! Wish more mobile games were like this. Kudos to the dev for having such integrity!
Absolutely brilliant tower defense game, no ads or purchases just a great quality well balanced game. Thanks devs
Very cool game! Lots of fun features and ideas.

I'm burnt out from micro transactions & p2w games, so it's refreshing that this game has NONE of that. Dungeon Warfare isn't the most sophisticated tower defense game I've played but it certainly is worth the 3 bucks. Another selling point for me is the difficulty. Some stages require several failed attempts before you can figure out the path to victory. Although I have not used it yet, you also get a rune, Breeze a little way in that reduces difficulty of a stage letting you exp farm if needed.

Way, way too difficult early on. Don't get me wrong, I like a challenge. Successful games build slowly into the more difficult levels and have more than one solution to complete each level. This doesn't. From about the 3rd or 4th level things get too difficult with only one solution that takes 5 or so attempts to find. I don't want to play the way the developers have decided I should play. I'd like to have some variety in how I complete the early levels.
Purchased, installed, started up once even after restarting my phone. Good game, when it worked.
Great game. Only problem is it taking over audio.
by far the best tower defense on Android right now. Tons of levels, traps, options and strategies. i don't think I've ever played a game on my phone for so long. definitely worth every cent.
Ready for the next installment!
One time payment and filled to the brim with content. Cant recommend enough for tower defense fans. A hidden gem in a sea of crappy MtX mobile games.
What a great game. Nice progression, lots of map variety, and the of replayability. Buy it!
Absolutely excellent game. I like that it let me play it for a fairly long time before asking me to rate it.

Dungeon Warfare combines physics and damage based traps, player XP, a persistent tower upgrade tree and optional difficulty modifiers with accompanying rewards into one solid TD game. No ads. No microtransactions. The full game at a fair price. We need more TDs like this on mobile.
Sick, nicely balanced, and fun game
I love the game. Please allow users to listen to audio of their choice, from another app, while using Dungeon Warfare. Oreo 8.1.0, on a Moto G5S Plus.

Good game, nice tip of the hat to bloons as well.
Excellent tower defense game without pay to win mechanics. The game seems well balanced and requires strategy to survive. Now Google, give us the ability to search for apps without in game purchases.
Best pure tower defense game you'll find.
If you enjoy tower defense type of games this is 100% for you! Been playing for just 30 minutes and I'm hooked. Super fun, lots of content/variety, just an overall great game.
The best tower defence game I have played on any platform. I want to be playing it right now.
This game is surprisingly difficult and super enjoyable. I have had a lot of fun playing it.
This is a trap game, the best I've seen on mobile, well worth the cost. Endlessly entertaining, I can't recommend it more!

One of the best tower defense games on Android. No ads. No pay to win. Just 
a one time purchase, and definitely worth every penny. Maps have multiple 
solution paths, so reply value is extremely high. As difficult as you want 
to be, with the rune system. Can't find a single flaw. 10/10

Can't tell if this game is brilliantly designed or on the contrary. There 
are some maps that either work stupidly well with what they're teaching 
you. And some... They don't even have good synergy because some walls were 
intentionally offset to force you to run something else. And some of the 
stuff you need isn't even unlocked until later. So was I supposed to enjoy 
it with a full kit of whatever I wanted or each level trying to teach me 
something new?

Great tower defence game and it really is what dungeon keeper should have been more like had EA not completely monitized it to death. Imho, this is up there with the best TD games such as Kingdom Rush. It is worth noting, there are zero micro transactions in this game.

Excellent game, easy to learn but difficult to master. Escalating challenge 
and a good value - no asinine IAP or DLC. No bugs or begging for money from 
the devs, just a solid, complete, extremely fun game at value price! Great 
features like pause, cloud save, pinch to zoom - why can't other game devs 
be so smart? Kudos - A+
Great TD
One of the best tower defense games I have played.
One of the best td.

content: Fun, unique tower defense game. The hordes of enemies have very satisfying deaths. The carnage reminds me of Smash TV. The audio is a nice touch.

best TD i've played. really fun and punishing

Mix Dungeon Keeper and a solid TD game and you get this game.  It's hard but not unfair and worth every penny.

content: Been a long time since a Android app has actually been so hard to put down. Quality and variety of traps is excellent.

A great, replayable, straight-up video game.
Thank you for an awesome game.

I am in love with this game and I don't understand how it isn't more popular. It plays a lot like Orcs Must Die but without the champions and it rewards you for using combos. My biggest issue with this game right now is that some traps are simply not viable at all while others are invaluable.

This game is definitely modeled after Orc's Must Die, and that's a great thing! This game plays perfectly from front to back. I usually hate writing reviews, but I want to support this game and hopefully additional content will follow. Fantastic game! Thank you! P.S. I found your hidden level!!
The pinnacle of tower defence

As a fan if tower defense games I am really enjoying this game. The leveling up is satisfying, and there's a lot of variety in what you can do.  My only issue is that when the game's audio is muted, I'm not able to play podcasts or listen to music with another app. Games like this are perfect when I can listen to music or podcasts, so it's unfortunate that I can't currently. Maybe with a future update it might be possible, and if it does I'll definitely give the game a full 5 stars!

Ever since the Bloon series went free-to-play, I've been looking for a pay-once alternative with the same depth. I first found Dungeon Warfare on Steam, but the PC version lacks the intuitive and quick touch control as well as other features. This is the definitive version. Buy.
This game is very imaginative and takes the tower defense genre to another level. And no in app purchases. Pay once and you got everything. I wish more games were like this...
